The
Feedback
--------

Not surprisingly, my Thursday quasi-eulogy for James Bond elicited tons of =
responses, not all of them
anti-Amazon. Some examples=E2=80=A6

=E2=80=9CA heartbreaking day, indeed. After everything that has happened to=
 Hollywood and California this past year=E2=80=A6 there can only be so many=
 more major surrenders before it is all wiped away forever.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=
=94A lawyer

=E2=80=9CMike [Hopkins] is furious at Jen [Salke]. He had to explain to Sea=
ttle why they needed to pay the producers that Jen was supposed to be manag=
ing in the first place.=E2=80=9D
=E2=80=94An executive

=E2=80=9CBarbara Broccoli couldn=E2=80=99t stand Jen. Wouldn=E2=80=99t sit =
with her at events or pose with her in photos or even mention her or Amazon=
 in speeches. Badly handled from the start.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94An Amazon ins=
ider

=E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m always here for your swipes at Amazon=E2=80=94frankly,=
 I'm surprised they haven=E2=80=99t delivered you a ticking package. But I=
=E2=80=99d love some context on how the [Ian] Fleming estate feels about al=
l this. As someone who works
with writers, the Broccolis seem like classic nepo babies who, depending on=
 who you ask, either protected Bond=E2=80=99s I.P. or diminished and exploi=
ted it. Sure, the movies are fine=E2=80=94some are good, some suck. But why=
 so much love for a family whose dad simply cut a great deal for rights to =
a property they had no hand in creating?=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A producer

=E2=80=9CThis franchise is not an easy lift for Amazon. It=E2=80=99s old an=
d it=E2=80=99s mostly international now. How do you reconnect a suave spy b=
orn out of the Cold
War with a young audience? The world order is so different now. Will there =
be Russian bad guys? Probably not.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94An executive

=E2=80=9CAs a Bond fan, I have to comment that the going-public-domain-in-2=
035 fact is a hell of a kicker. If they did come back with a rival Bond, it=
 would be an amazing reverse-Never Say Never Again situation! Never Say Nev=
er Again AGAIN!=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A writer-actor-producer

=E2=80=8A

Finally=E2=80=A6
----------

How did we survive January and February without a Jason Statham movie? Amaz=
on/MGM has
one, A Working Man, in late March, and it looks like another low-key hit, a=
ccording to The Quorum early film tracking chart=E2=80=A6

Have a great week,
Matt

