reak:break-word;"><tbody><tr><td style=3D"padding-bottom:32px;"><div style=
=3D"color:#000000;direction:ltr;font-family:&#39;Inter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;=
;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;line-height:150%;text-al=
ign:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;"><em>Not surpri=
singly, my Thursday quasi-eulogy for James Bond elicited tons of responses,=
 not all of them
anti-Amazon. Some examples=E2=80=A6</em><br/><br/>=E2=80=9CA heartbreaking =
day, indeed. After everything that has happened to Hollywood and California=
 this past year=E2=80=A6 there can only be so many more major surrenders be=
fore it is all wiped away forever.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94<em>A lawyer</em><br/>=
<br/>=E2=80=9C<strong>Mike</strong> [<strong>Hopkins</strong>] is furious a=
t <strong>Jen</strong> [<strong>Salke</strong>]. He had to explain to Seatt=
le why they needed to pay the producers that Jen was supposed to be managin=
g in the first place.=E2=80=9D
=E2=80=94<em>An executive</em><br/><br/>=E2=80=9C<strong>Barbara Broccoli</=
strong> couldn=E2=80=99t stand Jen. Wouldn=E2=80=99t sit with her at events=
 or pose with her in photos or even mention her or Amazon in speeches. Badl=
y handled from the start.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94<em>An Amazon insider</em><br/>=
<br/>=E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m always here for your swipes at Amazon=E2=80=94fra=
nkly, I&#39;m surprised they haven=E2=80=99t delivered you a ticking packag=
e. But I=E2=80=99d love some context on how the [<strong>Ian</strong>] <str=
ong>Fleming</strong> estate feels about all this. As someone who works
with writers, the Broccolis seem like classic nepo babies who, depending on=
 who you ask, either protected Bond=E2=80=99s I.P. or diminished and exploi=
ted it. Sure, the movies are fine=E2=80=94some are good, some suck. But why=
 so much love for a family whose dad simply cut a great deal for rights to =
a property they had no hand in creating?=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94<em>A producer</=
em><br/><br/>=E2=80=9CThis franchise is not an easy lift for Amazon. It=E2=
=80=99s old and it=E2=80=99s mostly international now. How do you reconnect=
 a suave spy born out of the Cold
War with a young audience? The world order is so different now. Will there =
be Russian bad guys? Probably not.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94<em>An executive</em><=
br/><br/>=E2=80=9CAs a Bond fan, I have to comment that the going-public-do=
main-in-2035 fact is a hell of a kicker. If they did come back with a rival=
 Bond, it would be an amazing reverse-<em>Never Say Never Again</em> situat=
ion! <em>Never Say Never Again AGAIN!</em>=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94<em>A writer-a=
ctor-producer</em></p></div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
